## Setup instructions for remote sync

This is a convenience that allows selectively syncing source files to a remote server.

## First time setup

1. Setup sync2vm for remote ssh connection
   $ ssh-copy-id username@server
   $ ssh username@server 'mkdir -p \$HOME/download/tqtc-coin-ci'

2. Update sync2vm configuration file:
   $ nano config

3. Create alias for the remote sync for convenience
   $ echo "alias sync2vm='~/sync2vm/sync2vm'" >> ~/.bash_aliases

4. Test remote sync tool
   $ sync2vm

## Advanced usage

To configure ignored files/directories:
   $ nano ~/sync2vm/ignore_modules

